Who is the tallest man alive?

The tallest man that lived was Robert Wadlow. Born in 1918, Robert was 8 feet and 11 inches in height during his adulthood. The shortest adult was Toiwasakami Kanesiro. An individual from Japan, Kanesiro was more than 2 feet and 7 inches in height.

How tall are people in Holland?

The average height of Dutch men is 1,80 meters (60.5 inches) compared to the American men that are on average 1,75 meters or 5,7inches tall. Dutch women, in their turn, have an average height of almost 1,70 meters (64,9 inches).
